<p>If you, as a publisher, are contacted by a new user indicating that they've encountered a <em>confirmation token is invalid</em> error, follow the procedure below:</p>

<p><%= cdn_image 'confirmation-token-is-invalid.png', alt: 'Confirmation token is invalid' %></p>

<ol>

  <li>
    <p>Navigate to the <em>Users</em> module by clicking the <em>Users</em> link in the <em>Sales</em> dropdown menu.</p>
    <p><%= cdn_image 'sales-menu-users-menu-item.png', alt: 'Sales menu: Users menu item' %></p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>Find the <em>user</em> record in question.</p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>Verify that the user is <em>confirmed</em>.</p>
    <p><%= cdn_image 'verify-user-confirmed.png', alt: 'Verify User Confirmed' %></p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>If the user is not <em>confirmed</em>, click the <em>Confirm User</em> link at the top of the page. Note: The link won't be visible if the user is already confirmed.</p>
    <p><%= cdn_image 'confirm-user.png', alt: 'Confirm User' %></p>
  </li>

</ol>

<p>NOTE: If the user was <em>confirmed</em>, they should have no problem logging into the site. They simply clicked the <em>Confirm my account</em> link twice. Note: The confirmation email describes this potential error at the bottom of the message.</p>

<p><%= cdn_image 'confirmation-instructions.png', alt: 'Confirmation instructions' %></p>
